'''TRAPPIST-1'''，即 '''2MASS J23062928-0502285'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://simbad.u-strasbg.fr/simbad/sim-id?Ident=2MASS+J23062928-0502285 |title=2MASS J23062928-0502285 |accessdate=2016-05-05 |archive-date=2019-04-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410035612/http://simbad.u-strasbg.fr/simbad/sim-id?Ident=2MASS+J23062928-0502285 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，是一顆表面溫度極低的[[超低温矮星|超冷紅矮星]]<ref name="Gillon2016">{{cite |url=http://www.eso.org/public/archives/releases/sciencepapers/eso1615/eso1615a.pdf |title=Temperate Earth-sized planets transiting a nearby ultracool dwarf star] |publisher=[[欧洲南方天文台|European Southern Observatory]] |format=pdf |accessdate=2016-05-05 |archive-date=2017-03-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170329022336/http://www.eso.org/public/archives/releases/sciencepapers/eso1615/eso1615a.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="eso.org" />，距離地球約{{convert|39.13|ly|pc|1}}，天球上位於[[寶瓶座|寶瓶座]]<ref name="NYT-20170222">{{cite news |last=Chang |first=Kenneth |title=7 Earth-Size Planets Identified in Orbit Around a Dwarf Star |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/22/science/trappist-1-exoplanets-nasa.html |date=2017-02-22 |work=[[纽约时报|New York Times]] |accessdate=2017-02-22 |archive-date=2019-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423155334/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/22/science/trappist-1-exoplanets-nasa.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2017年2月，天文學家在該恆星周圍發現7顆類地行星，是已知行星系統中擁有次多類地行星者，僅次於[[太陽|太陽]]和[[克卜勒90|克卜勒90]]<ref name="Witze2017" /><ref name = "Marchis2017">{{cite web | url = http://www.planetary.org/blogs/guest-blogs/2017/20170222-trappist-1-potentially-habitable-worlds.html | title = Wonderful potentially habitable worlds around TRAPPIST-1 | last = Marchis | first = F. | date = 22 February 2017 | publisher = [[行星學會|Planetary Society]] | access-date = 25 February 2017 | archive-date = 2017-02-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170225173824/http://www.planetary.org/blogs/guest-blogs/2017/20170222-trappist-1-potentially-habitable-worlds.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

==概要==
由[[比利時|比利時]][[列日大學|列日大學]]{{link-fr|列日大學天文物理與地球物理研究所|Institut d'astrophysique et de géophysique de l'Université de Liège|天文物理與地球物理研究所}}天文學家{{link-fr|米夏埃爾·吉隆|Michaël Gillon}}（Michaël Gillon）帶領的團隊<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ago.ulg.ac.be/index_e.php|title=AGO - Department of Astrophysics, Geophysics and Oceanography|publisher=|accessdate=2016-05-05|archive-date=2016-05-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160508095053/http://www.ago.ulg.ac.be/index_e.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>使用位於[[智利|智利]][[拉西拉天文台|拉西拉天文台]]的[[凌星行星及原行星小望遠鏡|凌星行星及原行星小望遠鏡]]（TRAnsiting Planets and PlanetesImals Small Telescope，TRAPPIST）<ref name="Guardian">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/may/02/could-these-newly-discovered-planets-orbiting-an-ultracool-dwarf-host-life|title=Could these newly-discovered planets orbiting an ultracool dwarf host life?|work=[[衛報|The Guardian]]|date=2016-05-02|accessdate=2016-05-05|archive-date=2019-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414014011/https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/may/02/could-these-newly-discovered-planets-orbiting-an-ultracool-dwarf-host-life|dead-url=no}}</ref>觀測TRAPPIST-1以尋找是否有系外行星環繞。藉著觀測[[凌日法|凌星測光]]，該團隊發現了三顆體積與地球相當的系外行星環繞TRAPPIST-1。較內側的兩顆已經被母恆星[[潮汐鎖定|潮汐鎖定]]，而最外側的行星可能位於該系統的[[適居帶|適居帶]]內或外側距離邊緣不遠處<ref name="eso.org">{{Cite web |url=https://www.eso.org/public/news/eso1615/ |title=Three Potentially Habitable Worlds Found Around Nearby Ultracool Dwarf Star - Currently the best place to search for life beyond the Solar System |website=eso.org |language=en-GB |access-date=2016-05-02 |archive-date=2019-04-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410145322/https://www.eso.org/public/news/eso1615/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.popularmechanics.com/space/deep-space/a20671/three-planets-life-outside-the-solar-system/ |title=Three New Planets Are the Best Bets for Life |work=Popular Mechanics |date=2016-05-02 |access-date=2016-05-02 |archive-date=2016-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160503121242/http://www.popularmechanics.com/space/deep-space/a20671/three-planets-life-outside-the-solar-system/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。發現這三顆行星的團隊自2015年9月至12月對TRAPPIST-1進行觀測，並且成果於2016年5月的《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》期刊<ref name="Guardian" /><ref>{{cite journal|title=Temperate Earth-sized planets transiting a nearby ultracool dwarf star |journal=[[自然_(期刊)|Nature]] |volume=533 |issue=7602 |pages=221–224 |year=2016 |doi=10.1038/nature17448 |last1=Gillon |first1=Michaël |last2=Jehin |first2=Emmanuël |last3=Lederer |first3=Susan M. |last4=Delrez |first4=Laetitia |last5=De Wit |first5=Julien |last6=Burdanov |first6=Artem |last7=Van Grootel |first7=Valérie |last8=Burgasser |first8=Adam J. |last9=Triaud |first9=Amaury H. M. J. |last10=Opitom |first10=Cyrielle |last11=Demory |first11=Brice-Olivier |last12=Sahu |first12=Devendra K. |last13=Bardalez Gagliuffi |first13=Daniella |last14=Magain |first14=Pierre |last15=Queloz |first15=Didier }}</ref>。

2017年2月22日，天文學家宣布在TRAPPIST-1周圍再發現4顆行星<ref>{{Citation|title=TRAPPIST-1 System – Discovery of Earth-Like Planets – Check123, Video Encyclopedia|url=http://www.check123.com/videos/12207-trappist-1-system-discovery-of-earth-like-planets|language=en|accessdate=2017-02-23|archive-date=2018-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804050257/https://www.check123.com/videos/12207-trappist-1-system-discovery-of-earth-like-planets|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2017/02/seven-exoplanets/517446/|title=Seven Earth-Sized Planets Have Been Spotted Around a Nearby Star|accessdate=2017-02-22|website=The Atlantic|language=en|archive-date=2017-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222205453/https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2017/02/seven-exoplanets/517446/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。除了TRAPPIST，參與發現這4顆行星的望遠鏡還有[[甚大望远镜|甚大望远镜]]、[[史匹哲太空望遠鏡|史匹哲太空望遠鏡]]等等。因此環繞TRAPPIST-1的行星數量達到7顆，並且可能至少有3顆行星位於[[適居帶|適居帶]]內<ref name="NBC-20170222">{{cite news |last=Shostak |first=Seth |authorlink=賽斯·肖斯塔克 |title=This Weird Planetary System Seems Like Something From Science Fiction |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/mach/space/weird-planetary-system-seems-something-science-fiction-n724136 |date=22 February 2017 |work=[[NBC新聞|NBC News]] |accessdate=1 March 2017 |archive-date=2017-03-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170302030705/http://www.nbcnews.com/mach/space/weird-planetary-system-seems-something-science-fiction-n724136 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。因此可以想像，如果該系統其他4顆行星表面如有液態水存在於某處，也許也是適合生命存在的<ref>{{cite web |url=http://spaceref.com/astronomy/temperate-earth-sized-planets-found-in-extraordinarily-rich-planetary-system-trappist-1.html |title=Temperate Earth-Sized Planets Found in Extraordinarily Rich Planetary System TRAPPIST-1 |date=2017-02-22 |author= |publisher=SpaceRef |accessdate=2017-02-11 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://exoplanets.nasa.gov/news/1419/nasa-telescope-reveals-largest-batch-of-earth-size-habitable-zone-planets-around-single-star/ |title=NASA telescope reveals largest batch of Earth-size, habitable-zone planets around single star |newspaper=Exoplanet Exploration: Planets Beyond our Solar System |access-date=2017-02-22 |publisher=[[NASA|NASA]] |archive-date=2019-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805111140/https://exoplanets.nasa.gov/news/1419/nasa-telescope-reveals-largest-batch-of-earth-size-habitable-zone-planets-around-single-star/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Bolmont2017">{{cite journal|url= https://academic.oup.com/mnras/article-abstract/464/3/3728/2514577/Water-loss-from-terrestrial-planets-orbiting?redirectedFrom=fulltext|title= Water loss from terrestrial planets orbiting ultracool dwarfs: implications for the planets of TRAPPIST-1|journal= [[皇家天文學會月報|Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society]]|volume= 464|issue= |pages= 3728–3741|doi= 10.1093/mnras/stw2578|year= 2017|last1= Bolmont|first1= E.|last2= Selsis|first2= F.|last3= Owen|first3= J. E.|last4= Ribas|first4= I.|last5= Raymond|first5= S. N.|last6= Leconte|first6= J.|last7= Gillon|first7= M.|access-date= 2017-03-01|archive-date= 2017-11-10|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20171110013428/https://academic.oup.com/mnras/article-abstract/464/3/3728/2514577/Water-loss-from-terrestrial-planets-orbiting?redirectedFrom=fulltext|dead-url= no}}</ref>。

== 發現與命名 ==
TRAPPIST-1於1999年由[[2微米全天巡天|2微米全天巡天]]（2MASS）發現<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.udel.edu/udaily/2017/february/star-connection/ |title=Celestial Connection |last=Bryant |first=Tracey |date=22 February 2017 |publisher=University of Delaware |accessdate=2017-02-26 |archive-date=2017-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170225050931/http://www.udel.edu/udaily/2017/february/star-connection/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，被編號為"2MASS J23062928-0502285"。編號中的數字分別是該天體在天球上的[[赤经|赤经]]與[[赤緯|赤緯]]，字母J則代表[[J2000.0|J2000.0]][[曆元|曆元]]。

之後比利時[[列日大學|列日大學]]的研究團隊於2015年9月至12月間使用位於南半球的[[凌星行星及原行星小望遠鏡|凌星行星及原行星小望遠鏡]]對該天體進行觀測，並於2016年5月的《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》期刊發表了他們的發現<ref name="Guardian" /><ref name="Gillon2016" />。該望遠鏡的英文縮寫TRAPPIST來自於比利時[[严规熙笃隐修会|严规熙笃隐修会]]，以及該團隊喜愛的[[修道院啤酒|修道院啤酒]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://foreignpolicy.com/2017/02/22/new-terrestrial-planets-discovered-by-international-scientists-international-collaboration-maybe-theres-some-aliens/|title=News So Foreign It’s Out of This World: Scientists Discover Seven New Potentially Habitable Planets|last=Gramer|first=Robbie|date=22 February 2017|publisher=[[外交政策_(杂志)|Foreign Policy]]|accessdate=2017-02-26|archive-date=2017-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170225172239/http://foreignpolicy.com/2017/02/22/new-terrestrial-planets-discovered-by-international-scientists-international-collaboration-maybe-theres-some-aliens/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.eso.org/public/news/eso1023/ | title = New National Telescope at La Silla—TRAPPIST to Scout the Sky and Uncover Exoplanets and Comets (eso1023 — Organisation Release) | date = 8 June 2010 | website = www.eso.org | publisher = ESO | accessdate = 4 January 2015 | archive-date = 2017-02-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170225211216/http://www.eso.org/public/news/eso1023/ | dead-url = yes }}</ref>。因為該恆星是凌星行星及原行星小望遠鏡發現的第一批系外行星的母恆星，因此發現者將它編號為 "TRAPPIST-1"。

系外行星的名稱則與發現的順序有關，並且第一顆被發現的行星是以母恆星名稱後綴字母''b''開始，第二顆後綴''c''，以此類推<ref name="planetnaming">{{cite arXiv |title=On the naming convention used for multiple star systems and extrasolar planets |date=2010 |last1=Hessman |first1=F. V. |last2=Dhillon |first2=V. S. |last3=Winget |first3=D. E. |last4=Schreiber |first4=M. R. |last5=Horne |first5=K. |last6=Marsh |first6=T. R. |last7=Guenther |first7=E. |last8=Schwope |first8=A. |last9=Heber |first9=U. |eprint=1012.0707|class=astro-ph.SR }}</ref>。TRAPPIST-1第一批發現的3顆行星的後綴''b''、 ''c''、''d''則是依照與母恆星距離由近而遠編號<ref name="Gillon2016" />。第二批發現的也以相同規則自''e''到''h''編號。

2017年2月23日，[[Google涂鸦|Google涂鸦]]的圖像以[[太陽系外行星|太陽系外行星]]為主題慶祝該系統第二批4顆行星的發現<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/science/exoplanet-discovery-celebrated-google-doodle-9901030|title=Exoplanet discovery celebrated with Google Doodle after three planets found|last=Radowitz|first=John von|date=2017-02-23|newspaper=mirror|access-date=2017-02-23|archive-date=2017-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170223100407/http://www.mirror.co.uk/science/exoplanet-discovery-celebrated-google-doodle-9901030|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 恆星狀態 ==
TRAPPIST-1是一顆[[超低溫矮星|超低溫矮星]]（Ultra-cool dwarf），光譜類型M8.0 ± 0.5。它的質量只有太陽的8%，半徑則只有太陽的11%，與木星接近<ref name="Gillon2016" />。它的表面溫度約2550 [[开尔文|K]]，年齡至少5億年（超過這個最小值則代表該恆星已經過了它年輕時期的活躍狀態。因為該類恆星的演化速度極為緩慢，它的狀態與年齡的關聯性不夠明顯。）<ref name="Gillon2016" />。相較之下，太陽年齡約46億年<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.universetoday.com/18847/life-of-the-sun/ |title=What is the Life Cycle Of The Sun? |author=Williams, Matt |date=24 September 2016 |work= |publisher=Universe Today |accessdate=19 February 2011 |archive-date=2014-04-09 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6OhiddzkA?url=http://www.universetoday.com/18847/life-of-the-sun/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，表面溫度約5778 K.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.universetoday.com/18092/temperature-of-the-sun/ |title=Temperature of the Sun |author=Cain, Fraser |date=23 December 2015 |work= |publisher=Universe Today |accessdate=19 February 2011 |archive-date=2010-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100829025937/http://www.universetoday.com/18092/temperature-of-the-sun/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

因為TRAPPIST-1的低光度，它的壽命也許可以達到12兆年<ref name="Adams2004">{{cite conference
 | last=Adams | first=Fred C.
 | last2=Laughlin|first2=Gregory|last3= Graves|first3=Genevieve J. M.
 | title=Red Dwarfs and the End of the Main Sequence
 | booktitle=Gravitational Collapse: From Massive Stars to Planets
 | pages=46–49
 | publisher=Revista Mexicana de Astronomía y Astrofísica
 | bibcode=2004RMxAC..22...46A
}}</ref>。TRAPPIST-1是一顆富含金屬的恆星，[[金屬量|金屬量]]（[Fe/H]）為0.04，即太陽的109%。它的光度只有0.05% {{solar luminosity|link=y}}，並且輻射能量大多在紅外線部分。它的視星等是肉眼不可見的18.80。

==行星系統==
2017年2月，天文學家宣布TRAPPIST-1周圍發現7顆[[類地行星|類地行星]]，並且其中5顆（[[TRAPPIST-1b|b]]、[[TRAPPIST-1c|c]]、[[TRAPPIST-1e|e]]、[[TRAPPIST-1f|f]]與[[TRAPPIST-1g|g]]）的體積與地球接近，另外兩顆（[[TRAPPIST-1d|d]]和[[TRAPPIST-1h|h]]）的體積則在[[火星|火星]]與地球之間<ref name="Gillon2017"/>。有3顆（e、f 和g）的軌道位於[[適居帶|適居帶]]<ref name="Gillon2017"/><ref name="nasa.gov">{{Cite press release |title=NASA Telescope Reveals Largest Batch of Earth-Size, Habitable-Zone Planets Around Single Star |publisher=[[NASA|NASA]] |url=https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-telescope-reveals-largest-batch-of-earth-size-habitable-zone-planets-around |access-date=2017-02-26 |archive-date=2017-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305055703/https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-telescope-reveals-largest-batch-of-earth-size-habitable-zone-planets-around/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="JPL image">{{Cite web |url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/spaceimages/details.php?id=PIA21422 |title=TRAPPIST-1 Planet Lineup |website=jpl.nasa.gov |accessdate=2017-02-26 |archive-date=2017-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303225725/https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/spaceimages/details.php?id=PIA21422 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="SPACE.com" />。其中較內側的6顆行星的質量總和占母恆星的0.02%，與[[木星|木星]]的[[伽利略衛星|伽利略衛星]]類似，因此兩者可能有相類似的形成歷史<ref name="Gillon2017"/>。
